SEC. 10. A new section, to be designated as Section 26-A of Presidential Decree No. 269, as amended, is hereby inserted to read as follows:

âSEC. 26-A.

Independence of the Board of Directors and Officers of Electric Cooperatives.

â To ensure the long-term business and economic viability of electric cooperatives, the management, operations and strategic planning of electric cooperatives shall, as much as practicable, be insulated from local politics.

âTowards this end, no person shall be elected or appointed as an officer or be eligible to run as a board member of an electric cooperative if:

â(a) such person or his or her spouse holds any public office;

â(b) such person or his or her spouse has been a candidate in the last preceding local or national elections;

â(c) such person has been convicted by final judgment of a crime involving moral turpitude;

â(d) such person has been terminated for cause from public office or private employment;

â(e) such person is related to any member of the electric cooperative board of directors, general manager and department managers within the fourth civil degree of consanguinity or affinity;

